      • shouldCreateVersionWithEmptyContent

        protected boolean shouldCreateVersionWithEmptyContent()
        Returns with true if the repository content should be tagged right after the initialization. Otherwise false.

        If true one could switch back to a version where the content is not available.
        The version ID for the above described version is ICodeSystemVersion.INITIAL_STATE.

        By default it always returns with false.

        Returns:
        true if the repository content should should be version after initialization. Otherwise false.

      • shouldCreateDbIndexes

        protected boolean shouldCreateDbIndexes()
        Returns true if the DB table indexes should be created on the repository startup, otherwise false.

        This method returns with true by default, subclasses may override this method.

        Returns:
        true if the DB indexes should be created by the current repository initializer otherwise false.

      • createAdditionalRevisionsForResource

        protected Collection<org.eclipse.emf.cdo.spi.common.revision.InternalCDORevision> createAdditionalRevisionsForResource(org.eclipse.emf.cdo.spi.common.revision.InternalCDORevision resourceRevision,
                                                                                                                       boolean metaRoot,
                                                                                                                       org.eclipse.emf.cdo.spi.server.InternalRepository repository)
        Creates and additional new object revisions for the given root CDO resource revision and returns with them.

        Returns with an empty collection by default.

        Parameters:
        resourceRevision - the brand new CDO root resource revision.
        metaRoot - true if the new resource revision argument is a meta root. Otherwise false.
        repository - the underlying repository which performing its very first start up.
        Returns:
        a collection of revisions representing a bunch of new objects that has to be added to the root revision argument.
